The paper focuses on privacy-preserving neural network prediction, which is a topic related to both cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the use of garbled circuits and secret sharing suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY).
